title: For Sale:  Original Beretta 92 "Step Slide" Rare 70's 1st Edition!!
postcontent: I have for sale a very rare 1970's Italian Beretta 92 "Step Slide" 1st Edition. This was the very 1st Beretta 92 series pistol ever made. Very few were produced(And even fewer imported into the U.S). Some key features are the rounded trigger guard, bottom or heel style mag release, 1911 style frame safety(IMO an improvement over the later slide safety), and "Step Slide". Only the very first batch of the 1st Editions have the step slide. Which was a weight reducing feature that Pietro Beretta decided wasn't worth the extra costs involved in machining. This pistol is in great overall condition(Personally, the best I've seen) and comes with original Beretta grips and magazine. Price is $2500 firm

postcontent: Following are observations about that arm and the holster.1- The holster is an original, period correct- piece that shows the expected deterioration of it's vintage but has been well stored and shows no rot. The safety lever is not as well finshed as the rest of the parts and appears to be a replacement.. it, too, does not match in patina or color.4- All of the checkering is better than expected.5- The grips are completly intact, with distinct checkering and the screws are 95 o/o...not at all buggered.6- The barrel is a good tight fit in the reciever/slide lock-up. It is grey and shows surface flecking but not pitting... there appeard to be about 60 o/o rifeling remaining...just off of 'sharp'.7- There is some looseness in the fit of the of the barrel link parts... this is not a problem and is generally expected. It is easily rectified with readily available and inexpensive parts. This condition is not dangerous but should be rectified sooner than later because it leads to excessive wear on other parts and can result in light hammer hits.8- the condition of the magazine is "good' it retains a high 80 o/o of original finish but is rough to the touch and does not drop free... it will take a bit of detailing to make it just right.For sale locallyI prefer cash.
